</div>
</div> 
It could be run. Corran may have run it. The portage involves a creative seal launch.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView73' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid8056">Welcome to Bob's World</a></b> (Class 5.0, Mile 6.7)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Welcome to Bob's World</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsPhotoDetailView269' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/17744/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/17744.jpg">
</a>
<i>Welcome to Bob's World</i></div><div>Photo by KE @ 1.65</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
One of the best and least portagable rapids on the run. Down the left side is the way, fast and hard.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView74' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid8057">Dr. Shoosh</a></b> (Class 5.0, Mile 6.8)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Bob Ross looking into Dr. Shoosh</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsPhotoDetailView273' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/17745/size/big/">
