</a>
<i>Bob Ross looking into Dr. Shoosh</i></div><div>Photo by KK @ 1.65</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
A great way to fall out of the Bob Ross gorge, I can't believe I don't have a picture. Its a low angle 15 foot slide with a hydro-esque hole at the bottom.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView75' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid8058">Spence Ridge Rumble</a></b> (Class 5.0, Mile 7.5)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Spence Ridge Rumble</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsPhotoDetailView277' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/17746/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/17746.jpg">
</a>
<i>Spence Ridge Rumble</i></div><div>Photo by KE @ 1.65</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
The longest and one of the best rapids on the run, this one is a little on the cardiovascular side of things.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView76' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid8016">Spence Ridge Trail</a></b> <br>
Take out on river left right below Spence Ridge Rumble and at the new footbridge. The trail leads 1.7 miles and 800 feet up to the parking area.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView77' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid8060">Twiggy's Revenge, aka Homies Slot</a></b> (Class 5.2, Mile 7.8)<br>
Seldom run now, since the floods of '04 made it very dangerous. There is a sneak on the left. Though easier and safer, it is sketchy too.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView78' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid8059">Cathedral Falls</a></b> (Class 5.0, Mile 7.9)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Cathedral Falls</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsPhotoDetailView281' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/17747/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/17747.jpg">
</a>
<i>Cathedral Falls</i></div><div>Photo @ 1.65</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
One of the best drops and the biggest one, this one is sweet and is in an other worldly setting.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView79' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid1966">Conley Cove Access</a></b> <br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Big pool at Conley Cove</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsPhotoDetailView285' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/17581/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/17581.jpg">
</a>
<i>Big pool at Conley Cove</i></div><div>Photo @ 1.65</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
Get out on the right after the scenic and long pool below Cathedral Gorge. Then hike the steepest mile of boat hiking in North Carolina.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView80' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid8061">The Spout</a></b> (Class IV, Mile 9.5)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>The spout</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsPhotoDetailView289' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/17748/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/17748.jpg">
</a>
<i>The spout</i></div><div>Photo of PM by NM @ 1.65</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
Just go far right and plop face first off this classic 10 foot spout into a deep pool.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView81' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid8062">Twist and Shout</a></b> (Class IV+, Mile 9.6)<br>
<div class='rapid-inline'>
<div class='controls'>
<h1>Twist and Shout</h1>
</div>
<div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsPhotoDetailView293' class='CPhotoDetailView-view CPhotoDetailView'> <div class='photo-inline'>
<a href="/content/Photo/detail/photoid/17749/size/big/">
<img class='riverdetail' src="/photos/archive/medium/17749.jpg">
</a>
<i>Twist and Shout</i></div><div>Photo of PM by NM @ 1.65</div></div> <br style='clear:both'>
</div>
</div> 
Good clean fun.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView82' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid6061">The Wall</a></b> (Class IV+, Mile 9.8)<br>
Great rapid with an elongate boulder wall near the bottom on the right that shoots a wall of water back left and off a 6 foot drop. Watch for wood on this one.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView83' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid1967">Pinch In Trail access</a></b> <br>
1800 feet in 1.5 miles. That would be absolute misery with a boat. Hiking down would be horrible to. Paddle to the lake at this point.<br>
<br clear=right>
</div><div id='zzqasc6tpu2pgpsRiverRapidView84' class='CRiverRapidView-view CRiverRapidView'> <b><a name="rapid1964">Linville Gauge</a></b> <br>
Right when you see the Hwy 126 bridge a few hundred yards down, grab a big eddy on the right where the gauge is located.<br>
<br clear=right>
